There's no special virus in China. Just the flu. Seasonal flu hits most countries around winter. Low Vitamin D from reduced sunlight. Kids go to school pass the flu around.

AI OverviewThe flu is more common in the winter because of a combination of factors  including:Weather: The flu virus's protective lipid layer hardens in cold  dry environments  allowing it to survive longer on surfaces and in the air. Drier air also dehydrates mucous membranes  making it harder for the body to fight respiratory infections.Indoor gatherings: People spend more time indoors during the winter  especially for holidays  which increases the risk of transmission.Immune system: The body's immune system is also affected by the winter

Now let's say that there is even a Norovirus event. Here's how common it is:AI OverviewYes  norovirus is very common:Global impactNorovirus is responsible for about 685 million cases of acute gastroenteritis each year  which is about 1 in 5 cases of the condition.US impactIn the US  about 1 in 15 people get norovirus each year. It's the leading cause of foodborne illness in the country.SeasonalNorovirus outbreaks are most common in the winter in countries above the equator  and in the spring and summer in countries below the equator.
